INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('122', '1', '2012-07-18 15:58:11', '2012-07-18 13:58:11', '	\n\nNatura Aperitivo Piscina Ballo Vintage Elettronica Notte\n\nTUTTI I VENERDI\' dal 1 giugno al 27 luglio\n\nSouth Beach sarà dedicato alle crew che hanno caratterizzato la stagione invernale del Bitte da Twist and Shout a Trash Milano, da Jungle Vibes a Smile, da Vietnam a BimBumBass.\n\nIn collaborazione con Arci Bitte e Associazione Culturale Bulkaria e Opposticoncordi\n\nDalle 19.00\nIngresso con uso Piscina Musica e Aperitivo\nArea Bambini\n\nDalle 22.00\nSi alza il volume e iniziano le danze nelle due sale\n\nSOUTH BEACH c/o LAGO SANTA MARIA\nVia De Amicis, 6 - Gudo Gambaredo - Buccinasco - Milano\n2km dal Forum di Assago\nhttp://www.southmilano.it/\n\n\n\nVENERDI 20 LUGLIO 2012\n\n\nSala 1: TWIST AND SHOUT feat ALESSIO GRANATA e ALE LEUCI + KETTY Vintage Style - Free hairstylist and makeup - get your retro look!\n\nLa serata più esplosiva del panorama milanese, la serata che ha dato un calcio al conformismo meneghino ed ha riportato in auge un genere che dopo cinquant’anni fa ballare ancora la gente bella di notte che cinquant’anni fa non c’era.\nUn’ epoca fatta di balli scatenati, surf, Cadillac, bei vestiti, gli anni delle primi mini-gonne e delle prime mini-cooper, gli anni del ballo del mattone, di Simone e del limone. I suoni di Motown, Sun, Decca, Stax, Sue e altre etichette che prima di chiudere i battenti ci hanno regalato gemme da consegnare ai posteri.\nhttp://www.facebook.com/twistandshout.50sand60s\n\n★ Dj Set by Alessio Granata, Henry Lazzeri ed Ale Leuci: dopo tempo immemorabile, tutti e 3 i djs di Twist and Shout insieme sullo stesso palco.\nFifties, sixties, rock \'n\' roll, rhythm and blues, garage, beat, doo wop, American Graffiti, boogie- woogie, twist, shout, loud, colonne sonore del ventennio più fervente di tutti i tempi che ormai da un anno fanno agitare bacini ed anche dei giovani milanesi, gente che ha voglia di ballare ritmi autentici sino all’esaurimento.\n\n★ FREE HAIRSTYLIST AND MAKE UP a cura di Ketty Vintage, acconciature e trucco d’epoca grazie alla bravissima Stylist Ketty Cinieri, che già molti di voi avranno potuto vedere all\'opera nelle più importanti manifestazioni italiane di Vintage, come quella di Castel Belgioioso.\n\n\n\nSala 2: A QUALCUNO PIACE GIPSY feat MATA HARI (ESP)\n\nQui riuniti nelle loro versioni Elettroniche contemporanee: il Jazz Americano, il suono dell\'Est Europa e le Musiche dal Mondo.\nLa tendenza Elettro-Swing, che infuria da Londra e in mezza Europa, cioè atmosfere retrò anni \'40 e vecchi brani Vintage rivisti su basi tendenzialmente House, ma anche Electro, Step e Breaks. A qualcuno Piace Gipsy, cioè un party alternativo, energetico e surreale, capace di rapire chiunque remixando il suono che attraversa l’Europa trascinando le culture locali con lo spirito gitano e mediterraneo. \nQuesta volta con la partecipazione Transglobal Bass di Mata Hari dalla Spagna.\n\n★ MATA HARI (ESP)\nLa sua musica \'TransGlobal Bass\' è un elettronica che spazia dall’Oriente ai Balcani passando per il Maghreb e le Americhe. Chi ha visto Filastine sabato scorso al Teramo sa cosa significa perchè insieme a lui è la co-propietaria nonché direttrice della Post World Industries. Ha vissuto a Copenaghen, Berlino e Sarajevo, città che ispirano i suoi djset; è stata resident 5 anni presso la Sala Apolo di Barcellona dove è la musa del collettivo United Global Beats.\nhttp://www.facebook.com/ pages/ Post-World-Industries/ 122954814468798\nhttp://soundcloud.com/mata-hari\n\n★ MADSOUNDSYSTEM (ITA)\nUn\'onda balcanica fatta di tube, trombe e clarinetti attraversa l\'Europa trascinando con sè tutto quello che incontra: swing, folk, dub, drum and bass, cumbia, reggae, ska, dupstep. A cavalcarla c\'è MadSoundSystem con il suo djset. Folk you!\n\n★ ROSANTIQUE (ITA) electrswing + Burlesque Show\nLa pin-up deejay paladina dell’Electro Swing in Italia.\n\n\n\nPROMOTER & FRIENDS:\n\nDj Sberla from B_Team\nMatteo Salt\n\nIngresso a Sottoscrizione 5 euro con uso piscina e musica\n\n', 'TWIST AND SHOUT + A QUALCUNO PIACE GIPSY @ South Beach', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'twist-and-shout-a-qualcuno-piace-gipsy-south-beach', '', '', '2012-07-20 13:27:38', '2012-07-20 11:27:38', '', '0', 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=122', '0', 'ai1ec_event', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('123', '1', '2012-07-18 15:58:11', '2012-07-18 13:58:11', 'MALIBU BAR \nVENERDI 20 LUGLIO\n\n*Ore 19:00\nDELICIOUS BOUDOIR\nAperitivo Finger Food a cura di\nKITCHEN CONFIDENTIAL\n\nBirra+Buffet Fonger Food-8€\nCocktail+Buffet Fonger Food-10€\n\n*DELICIOUS BOUDOIR ESPOSIZIONI*\n\n*Ore 22:30\nROCKGARDEN prod. & MALIBU\'bar\nPresentano\n\nROCK AROUND THE RIVER \n\"A \'50 Rock\'n\'Roll Exeprience\"\n\"I Party Rock\'n\'Roll sul LungoTevere\"\n\nLive Atc.\nTHE WILD STRINGS\n(RocknRollRockabilly)\nPresentazione ufficale del loro primo  Album dal titolo \n\"Rev it Up & Go Fast\" registrato e mixato nel Hombre Lobo Studio (RM) Aprile 2012-\n L\'Album si presenta in formato CD con 9 brani più una cover-dopo l\'uscita del 7\" dal titolo \"Keep on Rockin\'\" che include due brani inediti i \"The Wild Strings\" ripropongono in pieno il loro sound che fonde \nR\'n\'R /Rockabilly/Psychobilly/Countryil tutto miscelato con un pizzico di nostalgico Punk 77\' da cogliere tra le righe!!!\n\nDJSET All Night Long\ndjFoffy+djPieri\nSwingRocknRollSurfRockabilly\n\nLocation: \nMALIBU\'BAR\n\"Seriously Easy Going\"\nLungotevere della Farnesina ,00165/sotto Piazza Trilussa-Roma\nAperitif-CocktailBar-CarrebeanRum-DjSet-Live Acts\n\n§ FREE ENTRY §\n\nArt Direction:RockGarden prod.\n\nDon\'t Miss This Summer is Around The River..D', 'ROCK AROUND THE RIVER ps the WILD STRINGS Release party+DELICIOUS BOUDOIR', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'rock-around-the-river-ps-the-wild-strings-release-partydelicious-boudoir', '', '', '2012-07-18 15:58:11', '2012-07-18 13:58:11', '', '0', 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=123', '0', 'ai1ec_event', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('124', '1', '2012-07-18 15:58:11', '2012-07-18 13:58:11', '- COMBICHRIST  \n\n- AESTHETIC PERFECTION \n\n- SPECIAL AFTER SHOW\n\nCOMBICHRIST:\n\n“It’s beyond my personal demons, and extremely honest,” says LaPlegua of the fifth Combichrist album Making Monsters. With five albums, thousands of shows, and four full months in Europe touring with Rammstein (in front of hundreds of thousands of people), Combichrist has become a purely visceral creature, driven by instinct and emotion; stripped of all pretension. Its urgency - most evident in the raw and uncompromising new album – is fueled by expressions of lust, anger, pain and hate.\n\nPresenting a foreboding soundscape, the album kicks off with a hauntingly atmospheric instrumental “Declamation,” setting the tone for what is to follow: dark, stabbing synths; heavy, robotic beats; and swarming, buzz saw-style guitar sounds. Songs such as “Follow the Trail of Blood” (featuring Brendan Schiepatti of Bleeding Through) are baretoothed aggression; meanwhile the floor-stomping, first single “Never Surrender” proves to be aggressively catchy, with its metronome-tight rhythm through the verses, giving way to explosive choruses that is bound to pack dance floors. “Through These Eyes of Pain” takes a much subtler approach. Its echo-y vocal wash and glitchy beats conjure images like a mournful dream, exposing the man inside the monster. Though the moods displayed in Making Monsters are decidedly sinister, LaPlegua manages to portray these emotions in many different guises. Laden with hook heavy choruses, speaker-crushing beats, and LaPlegua’s trademark dark, aggressive vocals, this is an album that exudes honesty and the darkness that often comes with it.\n\nInitially cutting his teeth in the seminal Norwegian hardcore bands Fleshfire and Lash Out, LaPlegua segued out of that scene into the electronic music world with Icon of Coil. Originally a solo project, it morphed into a full band with the additions of Sebastian Komor and Christian Lund. Not only did IOC mark LaPlegua’s first major work with electronics and dance beats, but it also granted him wider exposure beyond Norway; IOC was LaPlegua’s first project to be released in the United States.\n\nIt wasn’t until 2003 that LaPlegua founded Combichrist - the project that would soon dominate his time. A departure from IOC\'s futurepop sound, Combichrist took LaPlegua’s hardcore past and electronica present and merged them into a singular, mechanical music monster. Without the compromise of the band dynamic, LaPlegua, who does everything in the studio himself on Combichrist releases, was able to explore whatever avenue he desired musically. What he found was a long dark road with plenty of twists and turns. The Joy of Gunz, LaPlegua’s first release as Combichrist, was quickly followed by two EP’s: 2004’s Kiss the Blade and Sex Drogen und Industrial.\n\nIn 2005, LaPlegua was back at it again, releasing the landmark album Everybody Hates You. Defying the dreaded sophomore slump, the second Combichrist full-length featured two tracks that would become club classics—“This Shit Will Fuck You Up” and “This Is My Rifle”—and was also the project’s U.S. debut on Metropolis Records. Further benchmarks were set with the release of the 2006 EP Get Your Body Beat, the title track of which landed Combichrist its first appearance on Billboard’s Top 10 Dance Singles chart.\n\nThe years that followed brought on two more full-length albums — What the Fuck Is Wrong with You People? (2007) and Today We Are All Demons (2009) — as well as a handful of additional EPs. On top of Combichrist’s many releases, LaPlegua has also logged countless miles, globetrotting on tours of Europe, South America, Australia, the United States and points in-between.\n\nThough Combichrist has kept him busy over the past seven years, LaPlegua has other interests that fill the rare breaks from his main musical project. The Atlanta, GA - based songwriter maintains Panzer AG, a sonic hybrid of Combichrist and Icon of Coil and even plays in a straightforward American rock \'n\' roll band, Scandinavian Cock. This affinity for Americana is also displayed in his love for hotrods and motorcycles. On his MySpace page, LaPlegua states, “I’m a Norwegian grease ball, and I\'m never afraid to get dirty!”\n\nWith Making Monsters, man and beast have combined, evolving beyond the demon it once was and into a greater, bigger and more malevolent force in music. This time, there’s no surrender.\n\n\nAESTHETIC PERFECTION:\n\nIt is not a comment on society.\nIt is not a forum for philosophy.\nIt is not your new voice.\nIt is not a revolution.\nWithout form, without ego or intention,\nAesthetic Perfection is music without a cause.\nInfluences are combined, songs composed.\nAudio is recorded, edited, arranged and mixed.\nMusic designed without purpose.\n\nhttp://www.aestheticperfection.carbonnine.com/about/\n\nSALA EBM INDUSTRIAL\nNOORGLO from decadence\nLUCA EW ( Electroworld ) \n\nSALA GOTH - ROCK\nERIC (Goth.it) \nFREDERIK\n\noltre alle solite sale Afro,Reggae,Goa\n\nINFO: info@rockplanet.it', 'COMBICHRIST + AESTHETIC PERFECTION', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'combichrist-aesthetic-perfection', '', '', '2012-07-18 15:58:11', '2012-07-18 13:58:11', '', '0', 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=124', '0', 'ai1ec_event', '', '0');
