INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('179', '1', '2012-07-18 15:58:12', '2012-07-18 13:58:12', '       www.boomfestival.org\n\n15 YEARS OF TRANSFORMATIONAL CULTURE\n\nMUSIC, ART, ENVIRONMENT, CULTURE\n\nBoom has 4 MUSIC STAGES (Dance Temple, Ambient Source, Alchemy Circle and the Sacred Fire). These are some of the music artists: \n\nGOATIKA presents Trance Levitation Show (RU)\nGOCOO (JAP) HILIGHT TRIBE (FRA)\nTHE PEAKING GODDESS COLLECTIVE (CHE)\nTJAK (POR) -Z- (GER – Alpha &amp; Antagon feat McCoy – SUN Project)\nFILTERIA (Suntrip – SWE)\nMAN MADE MAN (SPECIAL CLASSIC TRANCE LIVE ACT – UK)\nVIA AXIS (BRA)\nX-DREAM (REWIND the CLASSICS CONCERT – GER)\nYUDHISTHIRA (MK)\nAJJA (CHE – 3 HOUR SET)\nATYSS (FR) BEARDY (UK)\nCOMA SECTOR (ITA) DAKSINAMURTI (GER)\nDERANGO feat. PUROSURPO (SWE)\nDIGITAL TALK (FRA) ELECTRYPNOSE (CHE)\nFRACTAL COWBOYS (USA) GIUSEPPE (IT/DK)\nIANUARIA (AT)\nILLEGAL MACHINES (FR) \nJAHBO (DK) \nDJane LILL’LI (DK) \nKHAOS SEKTOR (POR)\nKINDZADZA (RU) \nMENOG (POR)\nNEUTRAL MOTION (JAP)\nDJane NUKY (POR)\nONKEL DUNKEL (DK) \nORESTIS (GRE)\nPARASENSE (RUS)\nPROCS (SWE) RAWAR (POR)\nSHORE BAR AXEL (GER/IRL)\nSHOTU (Hadra – FRA)\nAVALON (UK) \nBRAINCELL (CHE)\nBRIAN SENTIENT (USA) \nBUZZ_T(GER) \nCIRCUIT BREAKERS (UK/BRA)\nDICKSTER (UK) \nDIGOA (BR) \nFOG &amp; PHOBOS (ITA) \nKILLERWATTS (UK) \nLIQUID ROSS (UK)\nLOGIC BOMB (Tip World- SWE) \nLUCA &amp; DJane JAZZMINE (ITA/GER) \nLUCAS (UK)\nOLEG (HUN) vs TSUBI (HUN) \nRINKADINK (ZA)\nREGAN (ZA) \nSHANE GOBI (ZA – 3 HOUR SET)\nSPACE TRIBE (OZ) \nSWARUP (BRA)\nTHE FIRST STONE (BR) \nDJane THATHA (BR)\nTRISTAN (UK) \nU-RECKEN (ISR) \nZEN MECHANICS (HOL)\nACE VENTURA (SPECIAL BOOM 3 HOUR SET)\nCAPTAIN HOOK (ISR) \nECTIMA (SEB) \nE-CLIP (SEB) \nEGORYTHMIA (MKD) \nLIQUID SOUL (CHE) \nLOUD (ISR) \nPROTONICA (Iono – GER)\nTECHYON (POR)\n\nGALA DROP (POR) \nLAKAY (FRA)\nALEX R (POR) \nALEX TOLSTEY (SPA)\nALIJI (UK) \nBANEL (DK)\nBIRD OF PREY (USA)\nBRANDO LUPI (ITA) \nBRUJO’S BOWL (UK)\nCUBIXX (DE) \nEMOK (DK) \nEXPANDER (POR)\nEXTRAWELT (GER) \nGAUDI (ITA/UK)\nGORGO (HUN) GROUCH (NZ) \nHEDFLUX (UK) \nHUDA-G (ISR)\nHYPOGEO (ITA)\nJUREK PRZEZDZIECKI (Cocoon/Boshke Beats – POL)\nKAMINANDA (USA) KANGDING RAY (FRA/GER)\nMINDWAVE (ISR) \nOSHO (Echoes – ISR)\nPROTONICA Dj Set (GER)\nRADIOACTIVE.CAKE (Glitchy.Tonic – GER)\nROCKY (ISR) \nROBERDO RAVAL (SPA)\nSHEFF (ISR) \nSENSIENT (AUS)\nSWITCHST(D)ANCE (POR) \nTOM COSM (NZ)\nTRIPSWITCH (Special Midtempo Groove Set – UK)\nTWOFOLD (POR) \nVAL VASHAR (CRO) \nZEITGEIST (GER)\n\n\nA wide selection of environmental projects and technologies aiming to provide tools for change and living respectfully with the Sacred Earth.\n\nBoom Off the Grid: Taking one giant leap towards this goal, this year, Boom takes both its Healing and Sacred\nFire areas completely off grid – that’s 25 percent of the entire festival.\n\nYour Oil is Music: Boom’s plan for alternative energy has been evolving over recent years: in 2008, it launched the project: Your Oil is Music, collecting 45,000 litres of waste vegetable oil for its generators; preventing the emission of 117,000kg of C02 into the atmosphere.\n\nThe Boom Lab: Launched in 2010, the Boom Lab built five photovoltaic stations – a move that helped bring the festival even closer to becoming independent of the mainstream electrical matrix.\n\nPrinciples of Permaculture: Planting of edible gardens and flowers beds; nourishing the land using natural composting materials, implementation of ingenious ideas for growing organic food in hot, dry climates.\n\nWater: Boom’s system for recycling water has been in place since 2008 and is based on plants, bioremediation and evapotranspiration. \n\nBio-construction: All structures across the site built using sustainable materials including adobe, cane, stone, bamboo and straw-bale.\n\nComposting toilets: We use composting toilets from scratch on site, they generated 70,000 litres of organic, high quality liquid fertilizer for agricultural production.\n\nWaste Management: The Boom Ecoteam comprises a total of 150 volunteers that collect all the waste and recyclables on site. The team works around the clock collecting rubbish for the waste conversion facility, which compacts everything to send to the municipal system. There is also a system in place to recycle compost organics. \n\nFair Trade and Local Brands: Boom supports fair trade, opting for local brands and small companies\n\nEco-Art: The power of art is most profound when created with nature. Vast gardens become works of art as environ-artists work with natural materials, demonstrating sustainable and creative ways of connecting with nature. \n\nAWARDS: Boom’s dedication to creating an environmentally sustainable festival has reaped the following awards:\n• Greener Festival Award in 2008 and 2010 (for Outstanding Prize)\n• European Festival Award 2010 (for Green ‘n’ Clean Festival of the Year)\n\nLocalism: Basics such as fruit, vegetables, animal products, olive oil, water, local beer (made from natural ingredients) and materials for building and construction, are locally sourced.\n\nPermaculture principles drive the environmental program, allowing choices that enhance the ecology, economy and culture of the place while serving as a self-supply solution to the temporary resource shortfalls that many of us have experienced around the world.\n\nARTISTS and ART INSTALLATION CREWS CONFIRMED FOR BOOM 2012\n\nANDROID JONES (DIGITAL ART)\nARTESCAPE (PAINTING, DECORATION)\nBAMBOO DNA (BAMBOO INSTALLATIONS, LARGE STRUCTURES)\nCAREY THOMPSON (VISIONARY ART, PORTALS)\nDADARA (ARTIVISM)\nGAMELATRON (ROBOTIC LIVE SOUND ART INSTALLATION)\nLUGU TEST AREA (ECO ART/ TRASH ART)\nLUKE BROWN (VISIONARY ART, UV PAINTINGS, SCULPTURE)\nMOULIN AUX CHIMERES presents KaleidoAct – UNDERWATER MIRAGE (KALEIDOSCOPE ART INSTALLATION)\nMADNEOM (ART INSTALLATIONS)\nPATRICE HUBERT (KINETIC ART)\nRAM (ACIDIC GRAFFITI)\n\nLIMINAL VILLAGE (Boom\'s Cultural Hub)\n\nGUEST SPEAKERS CONFIRMED\n\nCHARLES EISENSTEIN (USA)\nCHARLES SHAW (USA)\nDANIEL PINCHBECK (USA)\nGRAHAM ST. JOHN (AUS)\nPETER BAMPTON (PT/UK)\nRICK DOBLIN (USA)\nROMIO SHRESTHA (NEP/IRE)\n\nWORKSHOPS\n\nALCHEMY SPINNING\nDANCE THE WORLD AWAKE (DANCING WITHOUT BORDERS)\nDANCES OF UNIVERSAL PEACE\nDANCING FREEDOM\nRAISING THE VIBE: A GATHERING OF DANCEFLOOR ENERGY WORKERS\nTRANCE DANCE\nYOGA TRANCE DANCE\n\nINTERACTIVE TALKS\n\nART AS MONEY\nGLOBAL ACTIVISM: WE ARE ONE\nHOOKED ON PLASTIC: TRUTHS ABOUT PLASTIC POLLUTION\nNEW CIVIL SPHERES AND SOCIAL CHANGE: FROM OCCUPY TO BOOM\nWATER TRAVELLERS: ONE YEAR AROUND THE WORLD OF WATER\n\nDISCUSSION PANELS\n\nTRANCE PANEL: 20 YEARS OF PSYTRANCE, 15 YEARS OF BOOM\n\nand much more!\n\nBoom\'s multidisciplinary, mind-expanding program is constantly evolving. Visit our website to discover more about each of Boom\'s areas - www.boomfestival.org\n', 'BOOM FESTIVAL 2012', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'boom-festival-2012', '', '', '2012-07-26 23:05:53', '2012-07-26 21:05:53', '', '0', 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=179', '0', 'ai1ec_event', '', '0');
